wasabi is a 2001 french action-comedy film directed by gérard krawczyk and written and produced by luc besson .   the film stars jean reno , michel muller and ryōko hirosue .   in france , it was released as wasabi , la petite moutarde qui monte au nez ( " wasabi , the little mustard that gets right up your nose " ) .   in south korea , the title was mistranslated to leon : the professional 2 .   the film gets its title from a scene where the protagonist , hubert fiorentini ( reno ) , eats a whole serving of wasabi at a japanese restaurant without flinching .